column5: Hey Wayne, i was looking at Google Maps satellite view today around Midland and the most current image with your field also shows an airliner flying overhead. Pretty cool image!  Click Here
Terry was playing with his drone again ?
Not chemtrails....he was having his crops sprayed. Air Canada did it for him last year but he wasn't too happy with the wait times.
Yah, I paid Google Earth to put that there, to mark my runway. Now there's no low flying excuses from guys cutting through my airspace! LOL
I see the carrot pile is finally gone.
Brian, Wayne is going with the times, now it’s all grass!
Wayne, that looks like an awesome property!  Of course now we all know where you live and you'll have to move!!! LMAO
Thanks Dax! Was just going to say.. now of course everyone knows where I live. Thanks Cast Away! Lots of hard work is all. Was nothing but a rough field and a forest 25 years ago.

A beautiful place for sure Wayne and a place to be proud of. I remember many past photos inside your shop, a first class operation. Sorry I should have PM'd this to you so everyone doesn't know your coordinates. A funny story for you, I met up with a cousin I haven't seen in 15 years and told him I fly RC planes and the next day he emailed me to ask if my plane is big enough for a second passenger. I sent him a picture of my 65" Mustang and said if you can fit you can go for a ride!
No harm fella! Was just razing you. Nothing much airplane going on these days, still deep into "Therapy" !
Thanks Raf! Only 1800 or so hours into it now.... probably 600 left to go. Car was torn down until there wasn't a SINGLE bolt left in the body.
Looking great Wayne... was up your way today.... Could not find the runway for my GMC to land on....

A beautiful place for sure Wayne and a place to be proud of. I remember many past photos inside your shop, a first class operation. Sorry I should have PM'd this to you so everyone doesn't know your coordinates. A funny story for you, I met up with a cousin I haven't seen in 15 years and told him I fly RC planes and the next day he emailed me to ask if my plane is big enough for a second passenger. I sent him a picture of my 65" Mustang and said if you can fit you can go for a ride!
Wow what an awesome car to restore Wayne. Do you still work on planes or have you retired?

Oh I'm supposed to be working on airplanes and have a few backlogged, but until I get my car (that Dad bought new) finished I can't fit anything in the shop. Hangar is a bit cold yet to work out there, but fortunately my boss is pretty easy to get along with... as long as I remember her Birthday, Valentines Day and a few other special days! LOL The car became my Therapy session and the bonus is I have something to keep after all the appointments are over! LOL It's come a LONG way in 2 years.
I would love to look over the facebook chronicle again. I was wondering how it was turning out. Looks very very excellent Wayne!
